import React from 'react'
import {ProjectsCard,ProjectContainer,ProjectsH1,ProjectsH2,ProjectsP,ProjectsWrapper,ProjectsIcon,SideBtnWrap,SideBtnLink} from './ProjectComponents'

const Projects = ({id}) => {
    return (
        <ProjectContainer id='projects'>
        <ProjectsH1>My Projects</ProjectsH1>
        <ProjectsWrapper>
        <ProjectsCard>
        <ProjectsH2>Chat-box</ProjectsH2>
        <ProjectsP>An app build to make conversations possible between relevant clients</ProjectsP>
        <SideBtnWrap>
        <SideBtnLink to ="//github.com/shraddhabelbase/Teacher-Dashboard-To-do-List-" target="_blank">
        Github</SideBtnLink></SideBtnWrap>
       </ProjectsCard>
        <ProjectsCard>
        <ProjectsH2>Katy-TrailApp</ProjectsH2>
        <ProjectsP>An app build to notify about Historic places in katy trail</ProjectsP>
        <SideBtnWrap><SideBtnLink to="//github.com/shraddhabelbase/katy_trail_app" target="_blank">
        Github</SideBtnLink></SideBtnWrap>
      </ProjectsCard>
        <ProjectsCard>
        <ProjectsH2>React-Components</ProjectsH2>
        <ProjectsP>A website for a store built using react components</ProjectsP>
        <SideBtnWrap><SideBtnLink to ="//github.com/shraddhabelbase/Website-React-" target="_blank">
        Github</SideBtnLink></SideBtnWrap>
        </ProjectsCard>
        </ProjectsWrapper>
        </ProjectContainer>
    )
}

export default Projects
